During the course, students will conduct a research project in groups where students implement geographical research methods and skills gained during studies to solve real-life problem. The research project includes all aspects from choosing suitable research methods and datasets to analysis and visualisation of results. After the course, students have the skills to conduct their thesis and work in groups.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop the analytical skills of the students. To develop the skills of using various geographical research methods and datasets. To increase geographical thinking and experiences for group work. Prepare master students for individual work with their MSc thesis and further research projects.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course the student knows how to: a) choose research, data analyses and spatial analyses methods and can justify his/her choice; b) use geographical literature and academic databases; c) apply research methods and carry out research individually; d) evaluate scientific studies and compose reviews; e) participate, plan and present group work.
